cques, Antoine, Yves, Michel, Jean Claude, Mireille, Jean Robert, Francois, Monique, Raoul, Serge.","French, Walloon, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and Mauritian:","from the personal name <i>Pierre</i>, French form of   Peter   (see also below). This is one of the most frequent surnames in Haiti (along with   Jean   and   Joseph  ) and in Saint Martin. It is also established elsewhere in the West Indies (e.g. in Trinidad and Tobago, Saint Lucia, Grenada, and Bahamas)."]},{"name":"Perrotte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Damien, Henri.","Altered form of French   Perrot   or   Perrault  , reflecting the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>.","French: from the feminine form of   Perrot  ."]}]},{"name":"Stephen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English spelling of the name of the first Christian martyr (Acts 6–7), whose feast is accordingly celebrated next after Christ's own (  26 December ). His name is derived from the Greek word <i>stephanos</i> ‘garland, crown’."],"variants":[{"name":"Stephan","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , preserving the vowels of the Greek name."]},{"name":"Steven","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , reflecting the normal pronunciation of the name in the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Stephen Perrot was born in 1360, in Pembrokeshire, Wales, his father, Peter Perrot, was 30 and his mother, Alice Harrold, was 20. He married Elen Howel about 1385, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1428, in Wales, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1360–1428":"1360–1428","1359–Female":"1359–Surnud","1362–1401":"1362–1401","1372–Female":"1372–Surnud","1382–1460":"1382–1460","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1330–1378":"1330–1378","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","about 1382":"umbes 1382","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1460":"1460","1372":"1372","1360":"1360","147